THE KEEPING OF THE BRIDGE

Now while the Three were tightening Their harness on their backs, The Consul was the foremost man To take in hand an axe: , And Fathers mixed with Commons Seized hat'chet, bar, and erow, And smote upon the planks above, And loosed the props below.
